1
00:00:02,150 --> 00:00:20,130
♪

2
00:00:20,130 --> 00:00:22,130
(singing in Japanese)

3
00:00:22,130 --> 00:01:44,240
♪

4
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,280
(bell ringing)

5
00:01:48,280 --> 00:02:00,230
♪

6
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:02,230
(crashing)

7
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:06,100
♪

8
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:07,220
It doesn't seem to be here.

9
00:02:07,220 --> 00:02:11,110
Yeah, Lance, I guess the
doctor must have it on himself.

10
00:02:11,110 --> 00:02:12,200
He was just here!

11
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:14,040
We must have just
missed grabbing him.

12
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:17,010
♪

13
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:19,030
Heh, don't worry my friends,

14
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:21,280
we'll find the good doctor
wherever he tries to hide.

15
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:23,000
He cannot escape.

16
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:30,060
♪

17
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:33,270
♪

18
00:02:33,270 --> 00:02:36,010
Every time we leave
the dojo to give a lesson,

19
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:37,050
I get depressed.

20
00:02:37,050 --> 00:02:38,090
A long time ago,

21
00:02:38,090 --> 00:02:41,060
that dojo had more than
50 students on the roster,

22
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:43,070
and now there's hardly
any students at all.

23
00:02:43,070 --> 00:02:44,290
Sure, Yoshi's
right, at this rate,

24
00:02:44,290 --> 00:02:47,080
kendo's going to
be a lost art form.

25
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,260
Due to the Meiji restoration,

26
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:51,150
it seems kendo has lost
a lot of its popularity.

27
00:02:51,150 --> 00:02:53,020
Kenshin, don't say
things like that.

28
00:02:53,020 --> 00:02:54,230
That sounds really negative.

29
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:56,240
I'll do anything
to keep Kendo alive,

30
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:58,220
even if I have to work
alone with nothing more

31
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,240
than a skinny arm.

32
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,130
Skinny arm?

33
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:03,130
I don't think you have
a skinny arm, in fact,

34
00:03:03,130 --> 00:03:06,230
I think your arm's
stronger than mine.

35
00:03:06,230 --> 00:03:09,210
Are you trying to
say I'm not feminine?

36
00:03:09,210 --> 00:03:11,240
(grunting)

37
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:14,170
How dare they make
fun of the weaker sex!

38
00:03:14,170 --> 00:03:16,080
Hey, Yoshi, did
I just hear Kaoru

39
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:18,030
say she was the weaker sex?

40
00:03:18,030 --> 00:03:21,150
Just agree with her
or she'll hit us again.

41
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:24,150
Yoshi, please do me a favor,
take these to the dojo.

42
00:03:24,150 --> 00:03:25,160
Bye!

43
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:27,030
Hold on, Kaoru!

44
00:03:27,030 --> 00:03:29,140
Man, she should do it herself.

45
00:03:29,140 --> 00:03:31,240
Darn it.

46
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,260
Sanosuke?

47
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:35,140
Anything happen
while we were gone?

48
00:03:35,140 --> 00:03:37,000
Unbelievable.

49
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,060
Rats, I can't win one!

50
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:41,220
You're unstoppable, it
isn't fair, I tell ya.

51
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:43,240
(laughing)

52
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:46,190
Looks like Sano is playing
chess with a foreigner.

53
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:48,170
You're right.

54
00:03:48,170 --> 00:03:52,050
Hello there you two, I...

55
00:03:52,050 --> 00:03:53,260
Kenshin, say something,

56
00:03:53,260 --> 00:03:55,110
I don't speak
another language!

57
00:03:58,170 --> 00:04:00,140
Hello!

58
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:02,000
Hello there, young folks,

59
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,050
my name is Hans, and
I come from Germany.

60
00:04:04,050 --> 00:04:06,160
It's nice to meat you.

61
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:08,030
Oh my, you speak English.

62
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:09,130
Sano, why didn't you tell us?

63
00:04:09,130 --> 00:04:11,080
Not only does this
guy speak English,

64
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:14,020
but he's an expert at shogi,
you know, Japanese chess.

65
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:16,090
I'm pretty good,
but he's unbeatable!

66
00:04:16,090 --> 00:04:18,080
I've lost five
straight games to him!

67
00:04:18,080 --> 00:04:20,070
Checkmate.

68
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:21,260
That makes six in a row!

69
00:04:21,260 --> 00:04:24,180
I don't know anybody from
Germany, do you, Kenshin?

70
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,280
No, I sure don't.

71
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:27,150
You must be
the master samurai,

72
00:04:27,150 --> 00:04:30,040
Kenshin Himura,
I've heard a lot about you.

73
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:32,090
Don't they call you
Battousai the Slasher?

74
00:04:32,090 --> 00:04:33,190
Huh?

75
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,260
That's really incredible,

76
00:04:34,260 --> 00:04:37,070
they even know all
about you in Germany!

77
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:39,040
I think you're mistaken, Kaoru.

78
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,080
Did you tell him, Sano?

79
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:42,030
There, beat that one!

80
00:04:42,030 --> 00:04:43,210
Oh, that's simple.

81
00:04:43,210 --> 00:04:45,180
(shouting)

82
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:49,290
I lugged this thing
all the way to the dojo,

83
00:04:49,290 --> 00:04:52,130
and there's only
one student here!

84
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:55,040
Huh, who's that guy?

85
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:58,070
Maybe this guy's come here to
make a challenge to our dojo!

86
00:04:59,110 --> 00:05:02,210
I, Yoshi Myojin, will
accept this challenge.

87
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:05,170
Huh?

88
00:05:05,170 --> 00:05:08,280
It can't be.

89
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:12,190
Y-Yutaro!

90
00:05:12,190 --> 00:05:13,240
Yoshi, it's you.

91
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,240
Yutaro, you came
back to see us.

92
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:18,060
I was in the neighborhood,
so I thought I would drop in.

93
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:20,030
Aren't you happy to see me?

94
00:05:20,030 --> 00:05:22,210
Yeah, but you're the last
guy I thought I'd see.

95
00:05:22,210 --> 00:05:25,220
So, how's your arm,
is it any better now?

96
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:28,260
Um, well, I'll tell you
how much better it is,

97
00:05:28,260 --> 00:05:31,030
it's good enough
to beat you, Yoshi.

98
00:05:31,030 --> 00:05:32,060
You game?

99
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:35,010
All right, let's go for it!

100
00:05:35,010 --> 00:05:37,010
(grunting)

101
00:05:37,010 --> 00:05:40,120
♪

102
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:43,130
It didn't take long for
Yoshi and Yutaro to go at it.

103
00:05:43,130 --> 00:05:46,020
It must be really nice
for them to see each other.

104
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:48,040
Why didn't you tell us
Yutaro was here, Sano?

105
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,020
What?

106
00:05:49,020 --> 00:05:50,120
Did you say something?

107
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,290
Never mind.

108
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:55,270
(grunting)

109
00:05:55,270 --> 00:05:57,180
Do you remember our match?

110
00:05:57,180 --> 00:06:00,200
Oh, who could
forget that, Yoshi.

111
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,020
I am ready for you.

112
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:03,080
I have been
training in Germany

113
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:05,030
for this moment
to finally arrive.

114
00:06:05,030 --> 00:06:06,140
Let's see what
you've learned.

115
00:06:06,140 --> 00:06:07,170
All right, let's go!

116
00:06:07,170 --> 00:06:09,180
(grunting)

117
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:14,290
♪

118
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:16,150
Oh?

119
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:19,100
Wunderbar, the boys are
practicing kendo together.

120
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:21,020
Let's watch.

121
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:24,080
It looks more like a fight
to me; knock it off you two!

122
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,150
Nah, Kaoru, leave them alone.

123
00:06:25,150 --> 00:06:26,210
What?

124
00:06:26,210 --> 00:06:28,100
They haven't seen each
other in a long while,

125
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,050
they need to get
back together again.

126
00:06:30,050 --> 00:06:31,170
-Right?
-Right.

127
00:06:31,170 --> 00:06:33,170
They're ecstatic when
those two are fighting.

128
00:06:33,170 --> 00:06:36,030
Leave them alone and let
them make up for lost time.

129
00:06:36,030 --> 00:06:40,080
♪

130
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:42,180
Hey, what's wrong Yoshi,
have you had enough yet?

131
00:06:42,180 --> 00:06:44,200
Hey, that'll be the day!

132
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,240
Yaa!

133
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,110
Keep your guard up, Yutaro!

134
00:06:47,110 --> 00:06:48,110
Yeah!

135
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:49,260
That's right, great!

136
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:52,040
I'm a little bit
worried about Dr. Hans.

137
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,220
He might just pop
a blood vessel or something.

138
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:56,110
Oh, he'll be just fine.

139
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:58,230
♪

140
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:17,260
♪

141
00:07:17,260 --> 00:07:20,260
Excuse me, Lieutenant Meldars.

142
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:22,290
I welcome you to Japan.

143
00:07:22,290 --> 00:07:24,210
We are celebrating
your arrival here

144
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:26,140
and we want you to feel
right at home here.

145
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:28,120
Welcome, my friends!

146
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,180
Minister Hoodle.

147
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:30,210
Yes, Lieutenant?

148
00:07:30,210 --> 00:07:33,020
I want all these guests
out of here right now.

149
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:35,040
There are some things I
need to talk to you about.

150
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:37,160
No, we can talk anytime,
let's have a drink.

151
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:39,220
Give me your wine
glass, Lieutenant,

152
00:07:39,220 --> 00:07:41,160
let's drink to the future.

153
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:43,270
Hey, did you flash your sword--

154
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:45,160
You cut clear
through the bottle!

155
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:50,000
Now, let's get
serious, minister,

156
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,030
I need you to clear
this hall immediately!

157
00:07:52,030 --> 00:07:54,130
Yes.

158
00:07:54,130 --> 00:07:56,090
Attention, stop the music!

159
00:07:56,090 --> 00:07:58,120
Everybody, you have
to leave right now!

160
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:00,200
I'm terribly sorry!

161
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,130
That's right,
everyone leave.

162
00:08:02,130 --> 00:08:03,290
I'll make it up
to you somehow!

163
00:08:03,290 --> 00:08:05,150
Keep moving!

164
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,040
You can clean that
stuff up later.

165
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:15,090
We want you all to
leave right away.

166
00:08:15,090 --> 00:08:18,040
Go on, get out, now!

167
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,140
(chuckles)

168
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,040
All right, everybody's gone.

169
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:25,050
I thought that you Germans
would enjoy a party,

170
00:08:25,050 --> 00:08:26,270
but I guess I was mistaken.

171
00:08:26,270 --> 00:08:28,220
Now, what was so important
that it couldn't wait

172
00:08:28,220 --> 00:08:32,150
until the festivities
were completed?

173
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:34,250
Know this, from
this time forward,

174
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:37,020
this consulate is
under our command!

175
00:08:37,020 --> 00:08:38,190
Anything that goes
through this consulate

176
00:08:38,190 --> 00:08:41,120
will go through us first,
is that understood, minister?

177
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:44,020
-What, how can that be?
-No questions!

178
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:45,280
From now on, you will
take your orders from me.

179
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:48,150
If anyone asks you
anything, you know nothing.

180
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:50,100
You will be richly rewarded

181
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:51,100
or severely punished,

182
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:52,270
the choice is yours.

183
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:56,050
But, how do you think you can
get away with that, anyway?

184
00:08:56,050 --> 00:08:58,150
I'm certain you have
seen this symbol before,

185
00:08:58,150 --> 00:09:02,020
it's the reason we can
do anything that we want.

186
00:09:02,020 --> 00:09:04,150
It can't be, that's the
symbol of the Black Knights!

187
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:06,110
So, you are
the Black Knights?

188
00:09:06,110 --> 00:09:08,190
We are not here
representing Germany.

189
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:12,080
We are in your country now to do
the bidding of our great leader.

190
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,290
We'll do anything
to attain our goal,

191
00:09:13,290 --> 00:09:16,060
so it's best that you
keep your mouth shut.

192
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:18,290
Of course I will, you can
count on me, Lieutenant Meldars.

193
00:09:18,290 --> 00:09:21,260
Just be sure to stay out
of our way, Minister Hoodle.

194
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:24,120
I have an assignment I'd
like you to do for us.

195
00:09:27,010 --> 00:09:28,250
Yes, what is it you want?

196
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:31,150
We believe that this man
is somewhere in Japan.

197
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:32,210
He is a German doctor

198
00:09:32,210 --> 00:09:35,090
traveling with a young
boy who is Japanese.

199
00:09:35,090 --> 00:09:38,080
I want you to find out
exactly where they are located.

200
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:43,270
♪

201
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:59,200
Why is Dr. Hans up so late?

202
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:02,000
It's got something
to do with that map.

203
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,190
He was looking in it the whole
time we were on the ship.

204
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:09,020
Hans is a doctor
who successfully

205
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:11,090
operated on Yutaro's arm.

206
00:10:11,090 --> 00:10:12,190
You think he's a
brilliant doctor,

207
00:10:12,190 --> 00:10:14,250
you should try playing
him at chess sometime.

208
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:17,150
I really don't understand
why they checked into a hotel,

209
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,260
they could have
stayed here with us.

210
00:10:18,260 --> 00:10:20,250
Maybe we should tell them that.

211
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:23,160
And now that Yutaro's arm
has healed completely,

212
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,200
we should throw
a party here at the dojo

213
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,210
to celebrate his
coming back here.

214
00:10:27,210 --> 00:10:30,210
That's a great idea, and we'll
thank Dr. Hans at the same time.

215
00:10:30,210 --> 00:10:32,100
Let's do it at Lenny's!

216
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:34,230
And that way, we can watch
the fireworks at night.

217
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:36,290
I'm not going.

218
00:10:36,290 --> 00:10:39,160
I have no reason to
celebrate anything.

219
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:41,290
Honestly, Yoshi,
don't be a party pooper.

220
00:10:41,290 --> 00:10:45,110
All right, I'll go to Lenny's
then and celebrate a little.

221
00:10:45,110 --> 00:10:47,120
But only if it's beef pot!

222
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,180
Well, I'm glad
you got over that.

223
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:55,050
♪

224
00:10:55,050 --> 00:10:56,210
Ever since I obtained this map,

225
00:10:56,210 --> 00:10:58,270
I feel as though
someone is after me.

226
00:10:58,270 --> 00:11:09,020
♪

227
00:11:09,020 --> 00:11:11,020
This isn't safe
in my possession,

228
00:11:11,020 --> 00:11:13,000
I'm going to have
to hide it somewhere.

229
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,080
I don't know what
the future holds,

230
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:16,160
and I can't jeopardize
Yutaro's safety.

231
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,290
♪

232
00:11:18,290 --> 00:11:21,040
Hm?

233
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:22,170
What are you doing awake?

234
00:11:22,170 --> 00:11:24,160
Sorry I startled you.

235
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:26,140
I couldn't sleep, sorry.

236
00:11:26,140 --> 00:11:29,040
Oh my, Yutaro,
I'm so sorry,

237
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:32,010
I didn't mean to
yell at you so loudly.

238
00:11:32,010 --> 00:11:34,260
I'm so jumpy lately,
I'm so sorry, Yutaro.

239
00:11:34,260 --> 00:11:36,080
It's all right, sir.

240
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:39,120
Hey, don't you have
a lesson at the dojo tomorrow?

241
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:41,160
You should go get some sleep.

242
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:43,180
All right, I'll do that.

243
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:47,210
♪

244
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,280
Hah!

245
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:54,000
Hah!

246
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,020
Hah!

247
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:56,090
Hah!

248
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:58,020
That's right, keep
your stance straight.

249
00:11:58,020 --> 00:11:59,260
Put some effort
into your movement!

250
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:01,070
Hah!

251
00:12:01,070 --> 00:12:04,040
Hah!

252
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:06,140
Hm.

253
00:12:06,140 --> 00:12:07,160
So...

254
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,240
(chuckles)

255
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,230
Match this.

256
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:11,280
It's not good enough.

257
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:13,030
Oh no!

258
00:12:13,030 --> 00:12:15,050
Looks like I win again, Sano.

259
00:12:15,050 --> 00:12:16,250
Rats!

260
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:19,250
There's your reward for losing!

261
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:21,250
Let's play just
one more game!

262
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:23,060
I won't lose this time!

263
00:12:23,060 --> 00:12:25,050
Yeah, if you
insist, be my guest.

264
00:12:25,050 --> 00:12:26,160
Try and beat that!

265
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:28,090
You only got
two, I win again!

266
00:12:28,090 --> 00:12:29,240
No, not again!

267
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:36,170
Here, congratulations on your
complete recovery, Yutaro!

268
00:12:36,170 --> 00:12:38,040
This wooden sword
is a gift to you

269
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,250
from the Kamiya Kasshin dojo.

270
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:40,280
Wow!

271
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:42,030
Thanks so much, Kaoru!

272
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:43,120
Yeah, that's wonderful.

273
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:46,040
This is a happy occasion,
we should all celebrate!

274
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:48,020
-Dig in, everybody!
-It's great.

275
00:12:48,020 --> 00:12:51,280
Listen up, Yutaro, I'm still
the number one student, got it?

276
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:53,170
And you're just
a second student!

277
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:54,290
What are you
talking about, dork?

278
00:12:54,290 --> 00:12:56,250
That's not the way you
address your superiors!

279
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:58,220
You're not my superior!

280
00:12:58,220 --> 00:13:01,060
You boys knock
that off right now!

281
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:01,455
Stop it!

282
00:13:01,455 --> 00:13:03,110
It's all right.

283
00:13:03,110 --> 00:13:06,060
Yutaro's very happy here
since we arrived in Japan.

284
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:08,050
They fight just like brothers.

285
00:13:08,050 --> 00:13:10,200
So, Kenshin, should we
get the hot beef pot?

286
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,160
Sounds like a good idea.

287
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:14,240
Hey, listen, if you two
are too busy fighting,

288
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:18,160
Sanosuke will eat up
everything on the table!

289
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:19,240
Hey!

290
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:22,120
You know, Sano, you're
nothing but a big pig!

291
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:24,200
Shut up.

292
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,120
Save some for us!

293
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:36,043
♪

294
00:13:36,043 --> 00:13:37,110
Did you find it?

295
00:13:37,110 --> 00:13:38,090
It's not here.

296
00:13:38,090 --> 00:13:40,080
Not here, either.

297
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:43,170
I guess we'll have to ask the
doctor where it is in person.

298
00:13:43,170 --> 00:13:45,160
Yutaro's arm was injured,

299
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,170
and now it's
completely healed up.

300
00:13:47,170 --> 00:13:50,210
Don't you think Western
medicine is absolutely amazing?

301
00:13:50,210 --> 00:13:53,290
Yes, you see, Dr. Hans is a
very famous doctor in Germany,

302
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:55,260
and compared
to German medicine,

303
00:13:55,260 --> 00:13:58,140
Japanese medicine is ten
years behind the times.

304
00:13:58,140 --> 00:14:00,190
No, I'd say 100
years behind the times.

305
00:14:00,190 --> 00:14:02,120
Now, now, let's not exaggerate.

306
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,270
(chuckles)

307
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:07,010
I would love to hear what Megumi
would have to say about that.

308
00:14:07,010 --> 00:14:09,130
Well, I really have to
study hard over there.

309
00:14:09,130 --> 00:14:11,270
I'm learning Western
medicine from Dr. Hans,

310
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:14,030
so I can be a doctor, and come
back here and save many lives--.

311
00:14:14,030 --> 00:14:15,180
-Yutaro!
-Huh?

312
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:17,240
All you talk about is
Western this, Western that,

313
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:19,000
it's sickening!

314
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,200
Do you have any idea
how annoying you are?

315
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,270
What did you just say?

316
00:14:21,270 --> 00:14:22,240
You know!

317
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:24,030
Calm yourself down, Yutaro.

318
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,140
Why should I?

319
00:14:25,140 --> 00:14:27,230
There is no East or West
when it comes to saving people

320
00:14:27,230 --> 00:14:29,180
who are suffering
from illnesses.

321
00:14:29,180 --> 00:14:31,030
There are many positive things

322
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:33,080
that come out of
both of our cultures.

323
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,210
The important thing
is to remember

324
00:14:34,210 --> 00:14:36,260
that all of us can
become good friends.

325
00:14:36,260 --> 00:14:38,200
I'm sorry, Dr. Hans.

326
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:42,010
So, do you think Sano will ever
beat you at chess, Dr. Hans?

327
00:14:42,010 --> 00:14:43,170
Sure I will!

328
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:44,230
I'll have you know,
Mr. Bigmouth,

329
00:14:44,230 --> 00:14:45,230
that I'll beat him!

330
00:14:45,230 --> 00:14:47,240
Tomorrow we'll have
a rematch and I'll win!

331
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:49,170
I'll play you as
often as you'd like.

332
00:14:49,170 --> 00:14:51,050
Sano's not a very good loser.

333
00:14:51,050 --> 00:14:53,020
(laughter)

334
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:58,130
See you tomorrow at the
dojo, all right, Yutaro?

335
00:14:58,130 --> 00:15:00,000
Right!

336
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:02,230
Then we'll see who the
best ninja is, Yutaro!

337
00:15:02,230 --> 00:15:03,240
I'll show you who's--

338
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,260
Oof!

339
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:06,020
What're you doing?

340
00:15:06,020 --> 00:15:06,389
You talk too much!

341
00:15:06,389 --> 00:15:08,010
(blows raspberry)

342
00:15:08,010 --> 00:15:09,010
Yeah, Kaoru is right!

343
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:11,160
Well, thanks again,
we'll be pushing off, now.

344
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,220
Good night, Dr. Hans.

345
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:15,010
(cacophony of farewells)

346
00:15:15,010 --> 00:15:17,280
We should head home, we could
watch the fireworks on the way.

347
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:19,120
What about dessert?

348
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:21,090
You still hungry?

349
00:15:21,090 --> 00:15:22,060
Hm?

350
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:33,100
I think it's great Yutaro
wants to be a doctor.

351
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:35,000
It's a wonderful profession.

352
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,090
You help so many
people feel better!

353
00:15:37,090 --> 00:15:39,050
It would be nice if you could
learn a little something

354
00:15:39,050 --> 00:15:40,170
from him, Yoshi boy.

355
00:15:40,170 --> 00:15:43,180
Hey, why do you always
take his side on everything?

356
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:45,280
If Yutaro is going to use
medicine to help people,

357
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:48,180
you can use a sword
to help people.

358
00:15:48,180 --> 00:15:50,250
You can help,
just like Kenshin.

359
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:53,210
That's right, I'll help
people better than Yutaro!

360
00:15:53,210 --> 00:15:54,240
That's the spirit!

361
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,060
What do you think, Kenshin?

362
00:15:56,060 --> 00:15:57,230
Whoa, what happened to Kenshin?

363
00:15:57,230 --> 00:15:58,200
Hey, Kenshin!

364
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:06,120
Those people at your Kamiya
Kasshin dojo are very nice,

365
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,170
aren't they?

366
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:08,210
Yeah, everyone, that is,

367
00:16:08,210 --> 00:16:10,240
except for Yoshi.

368
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,270
Hm?

369
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:13,050
(laughing)

370
00:16:13,050 --> 00:16:14,200
Well, if you ask me,

371
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:17,150
you and Yoshi look like
the best of friends, Yutaro.

372
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:19,080
Really, you think so?

373
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:24,150
♪

374
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,130
Who's there?

375
00:16:25,130 --> 00:16:27,030
Dr. Hans, I presume?

376
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:31,110
We've been looking all over
for you, I'm glad we found you.

377
00:16:31,110 --> 00:16:33,180
What in the world could
a German army officer

378
00:16:33,180 --> 00:16:35,140
possibly want from me?

379
00:16:35,140 --> 00:16:39,020
Please hand it over, Dr. Hans.

380
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:40,170
Hand what over?

381
00:16:40,170 --> 00:16:42,000
What're you talking about?

382
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,000
Fork it over, Doctor,
we know you have it.

383
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,160
Is it worth dying for in
a foreign country, Doctor?

384
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:54,020
We do not have time
for this, Doctor.

385
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:56,240
You people are not
regular soldiers, are you?

386
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:58,220
You have a good grasp
of the situation,

387
00:16:58,220 --> 00:17:03,100
I knew you were
a clever fellow, Doctor.

388
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,000
You are...

389
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,230
The dreaded Black Knights!

390
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:08,290
♪

391
00:17:08,290 --> 00:17:10,280
Yutaro, you must run away now.

392
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:12,030
No, I can't!

393
00:17:12,030 --> 00:17:13,150
I won't leave you behind!

394
00:17:13,150 --> 00:17:14,120
Don't argue with me.

395
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:15,180
Do as I say, now!

396
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:16,180
Never!

397
00:17:16,180 --> 00:17:17,210
Go!

398
00:17:17,210 --> 00:17:24,280
♪

399
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:26,280
(screaming)

400
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:33,080
♪

401
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:37,050
Dr. Hans!

402
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:38,120
Lieutenant, I found it!

403
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:41,180
Good, now complete
the job, Schneider!

404
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:42,220
Dr. Hans!

405
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:47,130
♪

406
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:49,180
Easy!

407
00:17:49,180 --> 00:17:52,030
What's the hurry?

408
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:53,080
Good night.

409
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:55,050
(laughing)

410
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,060
Now back off,

411
00:18:01,060 --> 00:18:05,250
I'm not about to let
you hurt this young man.

412
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:06,210
Kenshin!

413
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:08,040
You're not too bad, kid,

414
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:09,290
I didn't think anyone
in this backwood country

415
00:18:09,290 --> 00:18:11,080
could use a sword.

416
00:18:11,080 --> 00:18:13,270
This must be that famous
samurai we heard about!

417
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:22,260
Second Lieutenant Lance,
let me take care of him!

418
00:18:22,260 --> 00:18:24,010
Very well.

419
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:32,250
What are you waiting for?

420
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:34,210
Go on, make your move.

421
00:18:40,070 --> 00:18:42,000
Kenshin!

422
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,140
Yutaro!

423
00:18:43,140 --> 00:18:44,230
Hurry it up, Schneider!

424
00:18:44,230 --> 00:18:46,200
(screaming)

425
00:18:57,280 --> 00:19:01,010
Schneider, that is
enough, we're leaving!

426
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:02,250
(growling)

427
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,220
Kenshin!

428
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:09,280
Hey, Yutaro, are you all right?

429
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:10,260
Dr. Hans!

430
00:19:10,260 --> 00:19:12,180
They hurt Dr. Hans!

431
00:19:12,180 --> 00:19:14,110
(groaning)

432
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:17,070
He's seriously hurt, why did
they have to do this to him?

433
00:19:17,070 --> 00:19:18,210
Dr. Hans!

434
00:19:18,210 --> 00:19:19,290
What's going on, Kenshin?

435
00:19:19,290 --> 00:19:21,270
We have to get him to
Dr. Gensai right away.

436
00:19:21,270 --> 00:19:31,000
♪

437
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,040
Those bastards...

438
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:35,120
Oh God, please
don't let him die.

439
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:36,280
Yutaro.

440
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:39,200
Yutaro...

441
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:41,030
Yes, Doctor?

442
00:19:41,030 --> 00:19:42,110
I'm right here.

443
00:19:42,110 --> 00:19:44,070
You just gotta
hang in there.

444
00:19:44,070 --> 00:19:46,050
Forgive me, Yutaro,

445
00:19:46,050 --> 00:19:48,290
I put you in danger, I came
here to look for something.

446
00:19:48,290 --> 00:19:50,140
(groaning in pain)

447
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:52,220
That's the real
reason I came here.

448
00:19:52,220 --> 00:19:55,020
I had no right to hide
the truth from you!

449
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:56,100
Well, what was it?

450
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,220
Does it have something
to do with that map

451
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:59,120
that was taken from you?

452
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:03,120
I hid the final clue at
the dojo, just in case.

453
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:06,140
It's hidden in the
moon watching platform.

454
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:08,100
Hm?

455
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:09,280
Don't let those men find it!

456
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:12,220
Protect the incredible medicine
from falling into evil hands!

457
00:20:12,220 --> 00:20:13,180
You must promise!

458
00:20:13,180 --> 00:20:14,210
(groaning in pain)

459
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:16,190
Don't worry, I promise you!

460
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:19,270
Doctor, the operating room
is now ready for his surgery.

461
00:20:19,270 --> 00:20:23,080
Don't die!

462
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:25,230
Dr. Gensai and I
will not let him.

463
00:20:25,230 --> 00:20:27,210
He will be just
fine, you'll see.

464
00:20:27,210 --> 00:20:31,030
♪

465
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:33,020
Please, take good care of him.

466
00:20:35,190 --> 00:20:36,190
Cheers!

467
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:41,280
Even if the Japanese government
decides to take action on this,

468
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:45,100
you won't have a thing
to worry about, my friends.

469
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:47,020
Once we have this medicine,

470
00:20:47,020 --> 00:20:49,070
we will have the
world at our feet.

471
00:20:49,070 --> 00:20:50,170
What are you doing here?

472
00:20:50,170 --> 00:20:51,240
Get out of here at once!

473
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,270
Can't you see this
is a private meeting?

474
00:20:53,270 --> 00:20:57,000
You incompetent old fool!

475
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,270
(laughing)

476
00:21:00,180 --> 00:21:02,280
I wouldn't be so quick to
congratulate yourselves,

477
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:03,280
gentlemen.

478
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:04,210
Who's that?

479
00:21:04,210 --> 00:21:07,100
Where is she?

480
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:09,080
(shouting)

481
00:21:12,050 --> 00:21:16,040
Hold it.

482
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:18,010
(laughter)

483
00:21:20,230 --> 00:21:21,270
Gentlemen, I can help you,

484
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:24,020
in fact, you need me
to decipher the map.

485
00:21:24,020 --> 00:21:24,392
Really?

486
00:21:24,392 --> 00:21:26,170
And just who might
you be, my dear?

487
00:21:26,170 --> 00:21:30,130
My name is Misanagi,
head of the Sanada Ninjas.

488
00:21:30,130 --> 00:21:34,010
Nice to meet you, Misanagi
of the Sanada Ninjas.

489
00:21:34,010 --> 00:21:35,270
Had we know you were
such a lovely lady,

490
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:39,050
we would never have attacked you
in such an ungentlemanly manner.

491
00:21:39,050 --> 00:21:40,210
Please come over to join us.

492
00:21:40,210 --> 00:21:42,190
I hope we haven't upset you.

493
00:21:42,190 --> 00:21:44,130
It would be an honor
for us to meet you

494
00:21:44,130 --> 00:21:47,110
and discuss our future
business together.

495
00:21:47,110 --> 00:21:48,220
My pleasure.

496
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:52,180
Hm.

497
00:21:55,220 --> 00:21:57,120
I feel it, here it is.

498
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:02,090
This is the Doctor's journal!

499
00:22:02,090 --> 00:22:03,200
What is that thing?

500
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:06,010
Looks like a regular stone.

501
00:22:06,010 --> 00:22:08,100
Hey, Yutaro, what is
the miraculous medicine

502
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,070
that the doctor
was talking about?

503
00:22:10,070 --> 00:22:11,200
Can you tell us?

504
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:13,280
Miraculous medicine, does
this have to do with drugs?

505
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:17,020
Well, I don't
know about that.

506
00:22:17,020 --> 00:22:21,000
Right now, these are the
only two clues that we have.

507
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,240
♪

508
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:24,210
Yutaro?

509
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:26,050
I don't know what
this is all about,

510
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:28,080
but we'll help you
any way we can.

511
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:30,080
You can count on
all of us to help!

512
00:22:30,080 --> 00:22:31,190
Thank you all.

513
00:22:31,190 --> 00:22:37,120
♪

514
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:50,030
♪

515
00:22:50,030 --> 00:22:52,030
(singing in Japanese)

516
00:22:52,030 --> 00:25:02,150
♪

517
00:25:03,180 --> 00:25:06,060
♪

